{
  "action_id": "1329",
  "action_title": "Primates: Formulate diet to reflect nutritional composition of wild foods (including removal of domestic fruits)",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nOne before-and-after study in the USA\u00a0found that replacing milk with fruit juice in gorilla diets led to a decrease in regurgitation and reingestion. \nOne replicated, before-and-after study in the UK\u00a0found that when lemurs were fed a fruit-free diet aggression and self-directed behaviour were lower."
}

{
  "action_id": "1337",
  "action_title": "Primates: Change the number of feeds per day",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nTwo before-and-after studies in Japan and the USA\u00a0found that when the number of feeds per day were increased the amount of time spent feeding increased in chimpanzees, but hair eating also increased in baboons."
}

{
