  "action_title": "Amphibians: Separate sexes in non-breeding periods",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nOne replicated, before-and-after study in Australia\u00a0found that clutch size of frogs increased when sexes were separated in the non-breeding periods, alongside providing female mate choice, playing recorded mating calls and allowing females to increase in weight before breeding."
}

